---
name: monthly-review
description: 直近1ヶ月のTILエントリを一覧表示して振り返り、gitにもバックアップする。例: /monthly-review
---

Fetch and review TIL entries from the past 30 days, then save a backup markdown file to the til git repository.

## Steps

1. Calculate the date 30 days ago from today and the year-month (YYYY-MM)
{{- if .tilNotionEnabled }}
2. Search Notion DB_TIL for entries within that date range:
   - DB ID: `{{ .tilNotionDB }}`
   - Filter by `Date` property
3. Display entries grouped by Tags, then chronologically within each group:
   - Tag / Date / {{ .tilNotionTitleProp }} / {{ .tilNotionSummaryProp }}
{{- else }}
2. Read entries from the til repository:
   - Scan `{{ .tilRepoPath }}/entries/` for files matching the date range (filename starts with YYYY-MM-DD)
   - Also consult `{{ .tilRepoPath }}/INDEX.md` if it exists
3. Display entries grouped by Category, then chronologically within each group:
   - Category / Date / Title / Tags / Summary
{{- end }}
4. Add an overall comment: growth areas, recurring themes, topics to revisit
5. Save a backup markdown file to the til repository:
   - Repo: `{{ .tilRepoPath }}`
   - Path: `monthly/YYYY-MM.md`
   - File content:
     ```
     ---
     period: YYYY-MM
     entries: <number of entries>
     tags: [all tags that appeared this month]
     ---

     # 月次振り返り: YYYY-MM

     ## タグ別エントリ
     （タグでグループ化した一覧）

     ## まとめ
     （今月のコメント・成長エリア・継続テーマなど）
     ```
   - Run: `cd {{ .tilRepoPath }} && git add monthly/YYYY-MM.md && git commit -m "monthly: YYYY-MM" && git push`
6. Show the git commit result

## Notes

- If no entries found for the period, note that and skip the git step
- All output to the user and all content written to markdown files must be in Japanese
